deviceSupportVersions.instructions:
Your Mac needs an update to install virtual machines that use this version of macOS.

Here’s how you can install the update:

1. Head over to the [Apple Developer downloads page](https://developer.apple.com/download/).
2. Under “Operating Systems”, find “Device Support for macOS 26”.
3. Click the link below that item.
4. Double-click the downloaded DMG and open the installer. Follow the instructions.
5. Quit and relaunch VirtualBuddy. Then, try again.

Installing the latest Xcode beta will also install the required update.
deviceSupportVersions.title: Device Support Update Required
